en_142677_0	The authorities have decided to increase the fine for the inter-provincial passenger buses which operate without a due license.
en_142677_1	Accordingly, the current fine for the offence, 250,000 rupees will be doubled.
en_142677_2	Chairman of the National Transport Commission JanakaMallimarachchi says that the decision to increase the fine was taken at a meeting chaired by Transport Minister ArjunaRanatunga.
en_142677_3	At present there are about 200 buses that do not have inter-provincial transport licenses.
en_142677_4	The Transport Commission is of the view that this is a great injustice to the licensed bus operators.
en_142677_5	Also, this has caused frequent clashes among bus owners.
en_142677_6	JanakaMallimarachchi further stated that highest number of buses that are running without interprovincial licenses has reported from the Jaffna Colombo bus route.
